      <div id="main" role="main">
       <div class="region region-content">
        <div class="block block-system" id="block-system-main">
         <div class="content">
          <div class="view view-front-page-teasers view-id-front_page_teasers view-display-id-page view-dom-id-ebdc1c0cbd208e98706065a533054e22">
           <div class="view-header">
            <p>
             The Office of Chief Risk Officer (OCRO), formerly the Office of Audit, Compliance, Risk and Privacy (ACRP), strives to be a valued partner and advisor to management, faculty, and the Audit, Compliance and Risk Committee of the Board of Trustees.
            </p>
           </div>
           <div class="view-content">
            <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first frontpage-teaser-row">
             <div class="frontpage-teaser-image">
              <a href="/audit/internal-audit-services">
               <img alt="" src="https://acrp.stanford.edu/sites/g/files/sbiybj7501/f/default_images/scolumn_0.jpg" typeof="foaf:Image"/>
              </a>
             </div>
             <div class="frontpage-teaser-text">
              <h2 class="frontpage-teaser-title">
               <a href="/audit/internal-audit-services">
                Internal Audit Services
               </a>
              </h2>
              <div class="frontpage-teaser-body">
               Contributing to the University's success with ongoing risk assessments, constructive observations, and reliable opinions.
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
            <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even frontpage-teaser-row">
             <div class="frontpage-teaser-image">
              <a href="/compliance/ethics-and-compliance">
               <img alt="" src="https://acrp.stanford.edu/sites/g/files/sbiybj7501/f/default_images/sgarden_0.jpg" typeof="foaf:Image"/>
              </a>
             </div>
             <div class="frontpage-teaser-text">
              <h2 class="frontpage-teaser-title">
               <a href="/compliance/ethics-and-compliance">
                Ethics and Compliance
               </a>
              </h2>
              <div class="frontpage-teaser-body">
               Striving to uphold the highest level of ethical and lawful standards at Stanford.
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
            <div class="views-row views-row-3 views-row-odd frontpage-teaser-row">
             <div class="frontpage-teaser-image">
              <a href="/ERM">
               <img alt="" src="https://acrp.stanford.edu/sites/g/files/sbiybj7501/f/default_images/column1.jpg" typeof="foaf:Image"/>
              </a>
             </div>
             <div class="frontpage-teaser-text">
              <h2 class="frontpage-teaser-title">
               <a href="/ERM">
                Enterprise Risk Management (ERM)
               </a>
              </h2>
              <div class="frontpage-teaser-body">
               Enterprise Risk Management (ERM) provides a framework and processes for the identification, assessment, mitigation and monitoring of risks to the achievement of the University’s mission and goals.
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
            <div class="views-row views-row-4 views-row-even views-row-last frontpage-teaser-row">
             <div class="frontpage-teaser-image">
              <a href="/privacy/privacy-office">
               <img alt="privacy teaser" height="107" src="https://acrp.stanford.edu/sites/g/files/sbiybj7501/f/shared/images/teaser/privacy.jpg" typeof="foaf:Image" width="108"/>
              </a>
             </div>
             <div class="frontpage-teaser-text">
              <h2 class="frontpage-teaser-title">
               <a href="/privacy/privacy-office">
                Privacy Office
               </a>
              </h2>
              <div class="frontpage-teaser-body">
               Stanford University is committed to protecting the privacy of members of the Stanford community.
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
